public class ChangeStatus
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener

ChangeStatus class creates the UI for changing the status of user to active/inactive by the System Admin

This class will get all the active/inactive user based on user choice, then select the respective user whose status have to be updated.

This class also provide an entry point for the rest of the System Admin UI.

See Also:
RegisterUser, ChangeStatus, DeletePublication, control.controller.SystemAdminController, PMSystem, Serialized Form

actionPerformed

public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
This method will handle the action trigger by each button click in the ChangeStatus UI

reset button listener It will set the selected index of the groupCombo to 0 and remove all the elements in memberCombo and hiddenCombo

activeCombo button listener It will populate the memberCombo based on the selected value.

submit button listener It will update the status of the selected user to the opposite of the current status

logout button listener It will call the GeneralUSerController logout() and will change the frame to the HomePage

register button listener It will change the current frame to RegisterUser

deletePublication button listener It will change the current frame to the DeletePublication

assignRole button listener It will change the current frame to AssignRole

Specified by:
actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener
